<h2>What is Cazalla?</h2>

Cazalla is a tool for generating static websites. It is coded in PHP using Symfony2 components, so it may be specially friendly to Symfony and Twig users.

<h2>Installation</h2>

To start using Cazalla, first clone its repository:

<pre>
<code> git clone git://github.com/nacmartin/Cazalla.git </code>
</pre>

Then update submodules to obtain the dependences

<pre>
<code>
cd Cazalla
git submodule init
git submodule update
</code>
</pre>

Now you can start creating your site.

<h2>Creating a project</h2>

To create a project, run the following command:

<pre>
<code>
app/console cazalla:create --skeleton=tutorial
</code>
</pre>

<div class="note">You can ommit the --skeleton option if you want to create an empty project</div>

Now, in the <code>project/</code> you will see a fresh new project created for you. If you want to compile it, run:

<pre>
<code>
php tutorial.php
</code>
</pre>

And Cazalla will generate the statically generated content in <code>project/output</code>.
